WEBVTT

00:01.543 --> 00:02.711
♪ Oh, our love is so pretty ♪

00:02.711 --> 00:03.712
♪ Oh-e-oh-oh ♪

00:03.712 --> 00:05.881
♪ And I'm doing it right ♪

00:05.881 --> 00:08.884
♪ Numb in the face
from chemistry ♪

00:08.884 --> 00:12.054
♪ Nothing tastes better
than the sweet memory ♪

00:12.054 --> 00:13.722
♪ She's the head of committee ♪

00:13.722 --> 00:16.183
Ahh.

00:16.183 --> 00:19.394
[ Dramatic music plays ]

00:19.394 --> 00:24.399
♪♪

00:24.399 --> 00:26.735
Man: Hey.
Oh.

00:26.735 --> 00:29.363
[ Chuckles ] Hey.

00:29.363 --> 00:30.948
[ Breathing heavily ]

00:30.948 --> 00:32.783
[ Russian accent ]
Come look at this.

00:32.783 --> 00:34.952
Never seen
anything like it.

00:34.952 --> 00:37.621
♪♪

00:37.621 --> 00:40.249
Um...

00:40.249 --> 00:42.251
No, thanks.
Come on.

00:42.251 --> 00:43.669
♪♪

00:43.669 --> 00:45.546
I don't know
what the hell it is.

00:45.546 --> 00:46.880
[ Dog growls ]

00:46.880 --> 00:48.507
Wow, thanks for waiting.

00:48.507 --> 00:50.425
[ Barking ]
Hey, hey, hey.

00:50.425 --> 00:52.427
Luther, cool it.
Sorry.

00:52.427 --> 00:53.762
He's usually
such a sweetheart.

00:53.762 --> 00:55.889
Hey, let's go.
Wait, we just
got up here.

00:55.889 --> 00:57.140
Ow!
What is going on?

00:57.140 --> 00:58.725
That guy
is serial-killer creepy.

00:58.725 --> 01:01.478
Like, he tried to get me
to go inside with him.

01:01.478 --> 01:03.272
I'm calling 911.

01:03.272 --> 01:06.733
[ Dramatic music plays ]

01:07.985 --> 01:09.611
It's Bailey's
Army Reserve week.

01:09.611 --> 01:10.988
How's being
a bachelor going?

01:10.988 --> 01:12.239
Oh, I hate it.

01:12.239 --> 01:13.907
House is too quiet.

01:13.907 --> 01:16.243
Keep making an extra cup of
coffee for her without thinking.

01:16.243 --> 01:18.245
I-I did laundry
last night --

01:18.245 --> 01:20.080
not a single, weird,
frilly thing

01:20.080 --> 01:21.873
that I don't know how to fold
anyway.

01:21.873 --> 01:23.500
Kinda sounds like
you guys live together.

01:23.500 --> 01:24.668
Whoa! No!

01:24.668 --> 01:25.919
No, we're not ready
for that.

01:25.919 --> 01:27.754
She just stays over
sometimes.

01:27.754 --> 01:29.673
A -- A lot of times.

01:29.673 --> 01:30.924
♪♪

01:30.924 --> 01:33.010
Oh, my God. Did we accidentally
move in together?

01:33.010 --> 01:34.595
Dispatch: <i>7-Adam-15,</i>
<i>we have reports</i>

01:34.595 --> 01:36.555
<i>of suspicious activity</i>
<i>in Griffith Park,</i>

01:36.555 --> 01:38.348
<i>near the DWP relay station.</i>

01:38.348 --> 01:40.058
7-Adam-15,
show us responding.

01:40.058 --> 01:42.394
[ Siren wails ]

01:42.394 --> 01:45.188
Lucy: It's great that you guys
are so happy again.

01:45.188 --> 01:46.231
Nolan:
What is it they say?

01:46.231 --> 01:47.774
If you can survive
a secret marriage,

01:47.774 --> 01:49.318
you can survive
anything?

01:49.318 --> 01:50.319
Whoa.

01:50.319 --> 01:53.530
[ Dramatic music plays ]

01:53.530 --> 01:56.491
7-Adam-15 on site.
Signs of forced entry.

01:56.491 --> 01:57.868
We're gonna go in
and check it out.

01:57.868 --> 02:05.167
♪♪

02:05.167 --> 02:12.466
♪♪

02:12.466 --> 02:19.765
♪♪

02:19.765 --> 02:23.769
[ Beeping ]

02:23.769 --> 02:25.437
Lucy.

02:25.437 --> 02:26.688
Move!

02:26.688 --> 02:33.737
♪♪

02:40.994 --> 02:44.623
[ Explosion ]

02:46.416 --> 02:49.544
♪♪

02:54.341 --> 02:56.802
[ Sirens wailing,
police radio chatter ]

02:56.802 --> 02:58.053
You sure you're okay?

02:58.053 --> 02:59.554
Yes, sir.
Just a little banged up.

02:59.554 --> 03:01.390
That explosion took out power
to most of the Valley.

03:01.390 --> 03:03.934
Gonna take at least 12 hours
to restore it.

03:03.934 --> 03:05.560
Here come the feds.

03:05.560 --> 03:07.604
[ Siren chirping ]

03:11.775 --> 03:13.276
Matt,
how have you been?

03:13.276 --> 03:14.903
Me? Anxious.

03:14.903 --> 03:16.613
We've been hearing rumors
about a potential terror attack

03:16.613 --> 03:18.490
for weeks,
and now it's happened.

03:18.490 --> 03:19.825
Have you met Agent Fox?

03:19.825 --> 03:21.368
Sgt. Grey: No. Wade Grey.
Casey Fox.

03:21.368 --> 03:23.870
That's Sergeant Bradford,
Officers Nolan and Chen.

03:23.870 --> 03:25.956
Clearly, you're the ones
who found the bomb.

03:25.956 --> 03:27.207
Can you describe it?

03:27.207 --> 03:28.959
Not really.
All I saw was a timer,

03:28.959 --> 03:30.836
some wires, and then I was
running for my life.

03:30.836 --> 03:33.588
Same, but my impression was that
it was fairly rudimentary.

03:33.588 --> 03:34.965
Well, the bomb guys
will get in there.

03:34.965 --> 03:36.258
They'll take a look
once it's safe,

03:36.258 --> 03:37.509
and hopefully
there's something left

03:37.509 --> 03:39.177
that we can trace back
to a source.

03:39.177 --> 03:41.680
Of all the targets in the city,
why hit this place?

03:41.680 --> 03:43.765
I mean, there's no potential
for casualties.

03:43.765 --> 03:45.725
All they can do is knock out
power to the Valley.

03:45.725 --> 03:47.102
I don't know yet,

03:47.102 --> 03:48.728
but there is a possibility
that this attack

03:48.728 --> 03:50.105
is only the beginning,

03:50.105 --> 03:51.815
which is why the FBI
is taking over.

03:51.815 --> 03:53.567
Matt, this guy almost killed
two of my officers.

03:53.567 --> 03:55.318
We're not just gonna stand
on the sidelines.

03:55.318 --> 03:58.655
♪♪

03:58.655 --> 03:59.990
Okay.

03:59.990 --> 04:01.491
Let's "Super Friends"
the investigation --

04:01.491 --> 04:03.285
joint task force.
The first thing we need to do

04:03.285 --> 04:05.954
is talk to all the witnesses
who called 911.

04:05.954 --> 04:07.289
Thanks for riding
with me today.

04:07.289 --> 04:08.498
Yeah, of course.

04:08.498 --> 04:10.417
I'm happy to keep filling in
on the detective side.

04:10.417 --> 04:11.877
Because it keeps you out
of uniform.

04:11.877 --> 04:13.044
God, yes.

04:13.044 --> 04:15.338
I feel like I'm already,
like, 90 months pregnant.

04:16.673 --> 04:18.049
What?!

04:18.049 --> 04:21.470
Uh, Professor Meadows,
I am Detective Harper.

04:21.470 --> 04:23.221
This is Detective Lopez.

04:23.221 --> 04:24.639
You called about
an intruder.

04:24.639 --> 04:27.184
Yes. Yes.
Thank you for coming.

04:27.184 --> 04:30.479
[ <i>Indistinct talking on TV</i> ]

04:30.479 --> 04:33.190
I woke up in the middle
of the night,

04:33.190 --> 04:34.524
and there was someone
in my bedroom.

04:34.524 --> 04:35.776
Can you describe him?

04:35.776 --> 04:37.903
I can do better.
I sketched him.

04:39.738 --> 04:42.491
Now, where did I put
that drawing?

04:42.491 --> 04:44.034
Uh, he was an alien.

04:44.034 --> 04:47.454
I can...tell you that much
to start.

04:47.454 --> 04:49.414
You could tell
he was undocumented

04:49.414 --> 04:50.832
just by looking
at him?

04:50.832 --> 04:53.251
No, no, no, no,
not that kind of alien.

04:53.251 --> 04:54.961
No, he was, uh...

04:54.961 --> 04:56.755
Oh.

04:56.755 --> 04:59.132
He was a Heptapod.

04:59.132 --> 05:01.092
With cosmically
awful breath.

05:01.092 --> 05:02.427
♪♪

05:02.427 --> 05:05.680
Oh, and, um, how do you know
it was a he?

05:05.680 --> 05:08.642
Well, it was more
of a feeling I got.

05:08.642 --> 05:11.645
I-I certainly didn't see
any external genitalia,

05:11.645 --> 05:13.647
or I would have put it
in the sketch.

05:13.647 --> 05:15.607
Mr. Meadows, are you on
any medications?

05:15.607 --> 05:17.776
Why does everyone
always ask me that?

05:17.776 --> 05:19.486
Listen to me.

05:19.486 --> 05:23.490
An alien broke into my house
and stole my manuscript --

05:23.490 --> 05:26.952
<i>the</i> definitive treatise
on Los Angeles traffic patterns.

05:26.952 --> 05:30.580
Why would an alien
travel across the galaxy

05:30.580 --> 05:32.999
for a book on traffic?

05:32.999 --> 05:36.461
Understanding traffic is the key
to human colonization.

05:36.461 --> 05:38.088
Right.
Of course.

05:38.088 --> 05:42.175
You -- You think I'm crazy,
but I-I can prove it happened.

05:42.175 --> 05:44.928
The alien attacked me.

05:44.928 --> 05:47.514
I only survived because
I managed to lock myself

05:47.514 --> 05:48.849
in the bathroom.

05:52.060 --> 05:54.312
He's white, dark hair,
30s.

05:54.312 --> 05:55.605
With a scar
under his left eye.

05:55.605 --> 05:56.606
And he had an accent.

05:56.606 --> 05:58.567
Um...couldn't quite
place it.

05:58.567 --> 05:59.901
Well, it was Russian.

05:59.901 --> 06:01.903
Yeah, he sounded just like
Vladislav Ivanov.

06:01.903 --> 06:03.572
Who?
Lelush.

06:05.240 --> 06:06.950
<i>The super-hot model</i>
<i>who was trapped</i>

06:06.950 --> 06:09.327
<i>on that Chinese</i>
<i>reality singing show. I mean...</i>

06:09.327 --> 06:11.955
Can that be right?
Oh, yeah,
Lelush is super cute.

06:11.955 --> 06:13.748
No, I mean, the --
[ Door opens ]

06:13.748 --> 06:16.001
We need to pull them out.

06:16.001 --> 06:18.587
TID got a partial on a piece
of the explosive device.

06:18.587 --> 06:21.006
Prints came back
for an Ezekiel Freemont.

06:21.006 --> 06:22.799
That is not
a scar-faced Russian.

06:22.799 --> 06:24.801
So we could be dealing
with a terror cell.

06:24.801 --> 06:26.761
[ "Obnoxious" plays ]

06:26.761 --> 06:31.850
♪♪

06:31.850 --> 06:36.938
♪♪

06:36.938 --> 06:38.732
♪ I was gonna wait till later,
but I'll tell ya right now ♪

06:38.732 --> 06:40.317
Police!

06:40.317 --> 06:42.736
♪ You see you gotta step your
game up if you wanna get down ♪

06:42.736 --> 06:44.946
♪ Don't really matter
what you came for, man ♪

06:44.946 --> 06:47.324
♪ But I'mma raise my hand
saying... ♪

06:47.324 --> 06:49.451
Officer: Clear!

06:49.451 --> 06:50.744
All clear.
He's not here.

06:50.744 --> 06:52.829
Okay, now we go
into manhunt mode.

06:52.829 --> 06:54.789
Let's get a BOLO going,
and I want agents

06:54.789 --> 06:57.292
on the doorstep of everyone
that this guy has ever known

06:57.292 --> 06:58.668
by sundown.

06:58.668 --> 07:01.796
♪♪

07:01.796 --> 07:03.423
So, small world.

07:03.423 --> 07:05.675
Turns out, our suspect's
high school guidance counselor,

07:05.675 --> 07:07.344
Simone Clark,
is currently a trainee

07:07.344 --> 07:08.928
at the FBI Academy
at Quantico.

07:08.928 --> 07:10.513
So let's get her here
ASAP.

07:10.513 --> 07:13.767
[ Soft music plays ]

07:13.767 --> 07:15.018
[ Tires screech ]

07:15.018 --> 07:16.269
[ Glass shatters ]

07:16.269 --> 07:20.065
[ "Push That Limit" plays ]

07:20.065 --> 07:21.566
♪♪

07:21.566 --> 07:24.736
♪ Don't stop,
stand and deliver ♪

07:24.736 --> 07:27.572
Drifting is not
proper FBI technique!

07:27.572 --> 07:28.948
♪ Make them remember ♪

07:28.948 --> 07:31.409
Hey -- Oh. Aah!

07:31.409 --> 07:33.286
[ Tires screech ]

07:33.286 --> 07:35.580
♪ Yeah, God is my witness ♪

07:35.580 --> 07:37.499
♪ Can't handle my litness ♪

07:37.499 --> 07:38.500
What? Hey -- Oh.

07:38.500 --> 07:39.668
♪ Whatcha gonna do now? ♪

07:39.668 --> 07:41.419
♪ I'mma go all out ♪
Think we're good!

07:41.419 --> 07:43.380
♪ Whatcha gonna do now? ♪

07:43.380 --> 07:45.632
Whoo!

07:45.632 --> 07:47.467
Trainee, pursuit
is passing you!

07:47.467 --> 07:48.718
Oh, no.

07:48.718 --> 07:50.220
♪ Always climbing ♪

07:50.220 --> 07:51.096
♪ Keep on grinding ♪

07:51.096 --> 07:52.347
Here we go.

07:52.347 --> 07:54.349
[ Engine revs ]

07:54.349 --> 07:56.309
♪ I'mma go all out ♪

07:56.309 --> 07:58.019
♪ Whatcha gonna do now? ♪

07:58.019 --> 08:00.980
♪ Push that limit,
p-p-p-push that limit ♪

08:00.980 --> 08:03.066
♪ Gonna blow right past it ♪

08:03.066 --> 08:05.068
♪ P-P-P-Push that limit ♪

08:05.068 --> 08:06.361
[ Tires screech ]

08:06.361 --> 08:08.154
♪ P-P-Push that limit ♪

08:08.154 --> 08:10.824
FBI!
Out of the car!

08:10.824 --> 08:13.785
On the ground!
On your stomach! Do it now!

08:13.785 --> 08:15.620
♪ La la la-la-la-la-la ♪

08:15.620 --> 08:17.872
♪ La la la-la-la-la-la ♪

08:17.872 --> 08:19.249
♪ Push that limit ♪

08:19.249 --> 08:21.167
How'd I do?

08:21.167 --> 08:22.419
Pretty good, right?

08:22.419 --> 08:24.045
[ Vomits ]

08:24.045 --> 08:26.965
[ Coughing ]

08:26.965 --> 08:30.009
Where the hell did you learn
to drive like that?

08:30.009 --> 08:31.761
Claybourne High School
in D. C.

08:31.761 --> 08:34.347
I was a guidance counselor there
for 20 years.

08:34.347 --> 08:37.225
Taught Driver's Ed for
eight of 'em, till they realized

08:37.225 --> 08:40.228
I was using the time to teach
myself and my students

08:40.228 --> 08:42.230
advanced
driving techniques.

08:42.230 --> 08:44.274
I also coached
the wrestling team

08:44.274 --> 08:47.402
'cause I wanted to perfect
my hand-to-hand fighting style

08:47.402 --> 08:50.822
so I could pursue my dream
of becoming an FBI Agent.

08:50.822 --> 08:54.159
That's a...fun story.

08:54.159 --> 08:57.078
But the FBI has a very specific
way of doing things,

08:57.078 --> 08:58.913
and a 50-year-old --
48.

08:58.913 --> 09:00.790
48-year-old
former high school teacher

09:00.790 --> 09:05.587
with a "Fast & Furious" fetish
doesn't really fit our model.

09:05.587 --> 09:08.506
Did I make a single mistake
on the driving course?

09:08.506 --> 09:09.924
No.

09:09.924 --> 09:12.218
Did I successfully
pit-maneuver this car

09:12.218 --> 09:14.304
and put the suspect
under arrest?

09:14.304 --> 09:15.513
Yes.

09:15.513 --> 09:18.016
Alright, then I don't understand
what the problem is.

09:18.016 --> 09:21.519
Trainee...you are trying
to succeed at an agency

09:21.519 --> 09:25.190
where J. Edgar Hoover once fired
an agent for having acne.

09:25.190 --> 09:27.984
You're either FBI material
or you're not.

09:27.984 --> 09:30.361
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

09:35.784 --> 09:37.786
Simone Clark?
Yes, sir.

09:37.786 --> 09:40.455
Do you remember a student named
Ezekiel Freemont?

09:40.455 --> 09:41.998
Zeke. Yes, sir.

09:41.998 --> 09:44.959
He's the main suspect in
a terror attack in Los Angeles.

09:44.959 --> 09:47.504
You're going to L. A. to brief
investigative agents

09:47.504 --> 09:48.755
on Mr. Freemont.

09:48.755 --> 09:49.798
Happy to help, sir.

09:51.466 --> 09:53.885
Have yourself
a very good day...sir.

09:53.885 --> 09:55.136
Keegan:
Let's go, Clark.

09:55.136 --> 09:57.889
[ Up-tempo music plays ]

09:57.889 --> 10:04.395
♪♪

10:04.395 --> 10:06.856
Based on his history,
our suspect clearly shares

10:06.856 --> 10:08.775
several personality traits
with Ted Kaczynski,

10:08.775 --> 10:10.235
otherwise known
as the Unabomber.

10:10.235 --> 10:13.321
[ Door rattling ]

10:14.614 --> 10:17.325
[ Door creaks ]

10:18.618 --> 10:22.288
[ Grunting ]

10:26.209 --> 10:28.586
Whoops.
Don't mind me.

10:28.586 --> 10:30.880
I -- I'm just gonna
tuck in over here.

10:32.549 --> 10:34.801
Ooh.
Excuse me, handsome.

10:34.801 --> 10:37.053
No problem.

10:37.053 --> 10:39.472
As I was saying,
Ezekiel Freemont fits

10:39.472 --> 10:42.475
the classic mold of a high-IQ,
low-empathy psychopath.

10:42.475 --> 10:44.727
No,
that's not right.

10:44.727 --> 10:45.979
Did you say something?

10:45.979 --> 10:47.897
No, no, no.
Keep goin'.

10:49.607 --> 10:52.193
Becoming a bomber speaks
to his deep sense of anger

10:52.193 --> 10:53.278
and his impotency.

10:53.278 --> 10:54.654
But social and sexual
tendencies...

10:54.654 --> 10:56.197
Oh, Lord.
Excuse me.

10:56.197 --> 10:57.407
This is...
Who are you?

10:57.407 --> 10:59.909
I'm Simone Clark.

10:59.909 --> 11:02.245
I-I just flew in
from the Academy.

11:02.245 --> 11:04.956
I was Zeke's guidance counselor
for three years in D. C.

11:04.956 --> 11:07.834
Right. Step out so everybody
can see you.

11:07.834 --> 11:11.754
You clearly disagree
with Marlin's profile.

11:11.754 --> 11:15.049
I just don't recognize
the kid he's describing.

11:15.049 --> 11:17.010
Zeke grew up
in a violent home.

11:17.010 --> 11:19.679
Had sensory-overload issues
because of it.

11:19.679 --> 11:22.849
But I found him to be
a deeply empathetic person

11:22.849 --> 11:24.642
who isolated himself
from others

11:24.642 --> 11:27.145
as a protection mechanism.

11:27.145 --> 11:29.397
With all due respect,
you're a guidance counselor.

11:29.397 --> 11:31.858
I'm a trained
behavioral scientist

11:31.858 --> 11:33.318
with three decades'
experience.

11:33.318 --> 11:36.654
And I got mad respect for you,
even if you don't appreciate

11:36.654 --> 11:39.282
what a good guidance counselor
brings to the table.

11:39.282 --> 11:42.535
I've worked with literally
thousands of young men and women

11:42.535 --> 11:44.078
at their
most formative age,

11:44.078 --> 11:47.540
from future criminals
to future millionaires

11:47.540 --> 11:49.209
and everything
in between,

11:49.209 --> 11:51.544
and that made me
an expert on people.

11:51.544 --> 11:53.046
Where do you think Zeke
is hiding right now?

11:53.046 --> 11:55.465
Someplace dark and quiet.

11:55.465 --> 11:57.425
When the world
got overwhelming,

11:57.425 --> 11:59.636
he just went someplace
to hide.

11:59.636 --> 12:02.096
He feels safest
underground.

12:02.096 --> 12:04.432
Thank you for your insight,
Trainee Clark,

12:04.432 --> 12:07.393
but I'm gonna trust our profiler
on this one.

12:07.393 --> 12:10.772
The guy that you knew in D. C.,
he's no longer the same guy.

12:10.772 --> 12:13.149
We think that he's part
of a terrorist cell

12:13.149 --> 12:15.193
intending to strike this city
again.

12:15.193 --> 12:17.278
And we need to catch him
before they set off a bomb --

12:17.278 --> 12:18.821
one that kills innocent people
this time.

12:18.821 --> 12:20.281
So let's get to work.

12:20.281 --> 12:23.284
[ Indistinct conversations ]

12:26.496 --> 12:28.748
[ Sighs ]

12:28.748 --> 12:33.795
Um...I just want to say, I am so
sorry for speaking out of turn.

12:33.795 --> 12:37.257
So, w-what can I do now?
I mean, how can I help?

12:37.257 --> 12:39.175
Y-You can't.

12:39.175 --> 12:40.760
You should just go back
to the Academy.

12:40.760 --> 12:42.762
The travel office
is on the fourth floor.

12:42.762 --> 12:45.098
They'll give you a voucher for
a coach seat back to Virginia.

12:45.098 --> 12:47.183
So, no private jet?

12:47.183 --> 12:49.143
Pr--

12:49.143 --> 12:51.020
Je-- No.

12:51.020 --> 12:52.105
Excuse me.

13:01.572 --> 13:04.492
That was pretty brave,
the way you spoke up in there.

13:04.492 --> 13:06.202
[ Chuckles ]

13:06.202 --> 13:09.789
Thank you, but I don't think
I did myself any favors.

13:09.789 --> 13:11.833
John Nolan.
Simone Clark.

13:11.833 --> 13:14.711
Did you hang back 'cause you
wanted to get my phone number?

13:14.711 --> 13:16.421
No, ma'am.
Just to tell you,

13:16.421 --> 13:18.756
I think they were wrong to
dismiss your insight so quickly.

13:18.756 --> 13:20.091
You're the only one
in that room

13:20.091 --> 13:22.135
who actually knows
our Mr. Freemont.

13:22.135 --> 13:24.554
In my book, that makes you
the only real expert.

13:24.554 --> 13:26.306
Ooh. Keep talkin'.

13:26.306 --> 13:28.057
Well, if you're not in a rush
to get back to Quantico,

13:28.057 --> 13:30.101
how would you like to ride
with me the rest of my shift,

13:30.101 --> 13:31.352
help us find our suspect?

13:31.352 --> 13:34.397
[ Up-tempo music plays ]

13:34.397 --> 13:35.940
I'd love to.

13:35.940 --> 13:37.108
This way.

13:37.108 --> 13:38.943
♪♪

13:38.943 --> 13:40.653
Simone: How long you been
on the job?

13:40.653 --> 13:41.946
Nolan:
Only a couple years.

13:41.946 --> 13:45.324
I was just the oldest rookie
in the LAPD.

13:45.324 --> 13:47.035
What? That's funny

13:47.035 --> 13:50.705
because I'm the oldest trainee
at the Academy.

13:50.705 --> 13:53.916
So, why'd you change course
and sign up?

13:53.916 --> 13:56.627
Found myself in the middle
of a bank robbery.

13:56.627 --> 13:58.254
What?
Helping the people
on the inside

13:58.254 --> 13:59.839
made me want to do
more of it.

13:59.839 --> 14:01.257
What about yourself?

14:01.257 --> 14:03.509
I've always wanted to be
an FBI agent,

14:03.509 --> 14:06.095
but I ended up on an off-ramp
when I found out

14:06.095 --> 14:07.889
I was pregnant
with the twins.

14:07.889 --> 14:12.435
They in college now, so time for
Mama to finish what she started.

14:12.435 --> 14:13.978
It's not easy, though,
trying to keep up

14:13.978 --> 14:15.605
with these 20-somethings.

14:15.605 --> 14:16.731
Sheesh.

14:16.731 --> 14:18.983
Every day, I am determined
to beat them,

14:18.983 --> 14:22.195
and every night, I crawl into
bed feeling beaten.

14:22.195 --> 14:23.863
[ Chuckles ]

14:23.863 --> 14:26.074
Can I offer you
some hard-won advice?

14:26.074 --> 14:27.408
Please.

14:27.408 --> 14:29.660
You are never gonna beat them
at being 20-something.

14:29.660 --> 14:31.370
But what you lack
in flexibility

14:31.370 --> 14:33.247
or the ability to run up
a flight of stairs

14:33.247 --> 14:34.749
without getting winded...
[ Chuckles ]

14:34.749 --> 14:37.835
...you more than make up for
in life experience.

14:37.835 --> 14:41.005
And that puts you way ahead of
the curve, day one on the job.

14:43.257 --> 14:45.426
I appreciate that.
Thank you.

14:45.426 --> 14:46.969
Anytime.

14:50.348 --> 14:51.891
Alright.

14:51.891 --> 14:54.977
This is the closest tunnel
to Zeke's apartment.

14:54.977 --> 14:57.105
I'll go check it out.
I'mma come with you.

14:57.105 --> 14:58.981
No, it's not safe.
You're not even armed.

14:58.981 --> 15:00.775
I'm telling you,
I know this kid.

15:00.775 --> 15:02.360
He's not
a violent person.

15:02.360 --> 15:04.821
And the bomb that nearly
killed me says differently.

15:04.821 --> 15:06.572
Well --
Stay here.

15:10.910 --> 15:13.037
[ Dramatic music plays ]

15:13.037 --> 15:16.207
♪♪

15:16.207 --> 15:17.875
[ Gate creaks open ]

15:17.875 --> 15:21.796
♪♪

15:21.796 --> 15:30.304
♪♪

15:30.304 --> 15:38.813
♪♪

15:38.813 --> 15:41.524
[ Grunts ]

15:41.524 --> 15:44.110
7-Adam-15, I have eyes
on our bombing suspect.

15:44.110 --> 15:45.862
Heading east
toward King Street.

15:46.904 --> 15:48.739
Zeke. Zeke!

15:48.739 --> 15:51.868
♪♪

15:51.868 --> 15:53.953
[ Engine starts ]

15:53.953 --> 15:57.206
[ Tires screech ]

16:00.543 --> 16:02.003
Don't even think
about it.

16:02.003 --> 16:03.504
I got him.

16:03.504 --> 16:05.006
[ Grunts ]

16:05.006 --> 16:06.799
Did you just steal
my police vehicle?

16:06.799 --> 16:09.927
No. I borrowed it
to catch a fleeing suspect.

16:09.927 --> 16:11.846
You're welcome.
[ Handcuffs click ]

16:11.846 --> 16:14.348
Miss Clark, is that you?

16:14.348 --> 16:16.392
Yes, honey.

16:16.392 --> 16:18.269
Please don't let that man
kill me.

16:18.269 --> 16:20.271
[ Dramatic music plays ]

16:20.271 --> 16:21.731
What man?

16:21.731 --> 16:31.741
♪♪

16:31.741 --> 16:35.620
[ Man moaning loudly ]

16:35.620 --> 16:45.588
♪♪

16:45.588 --> 16:47.757
[ Sobbing ]

16:47.757 --> 16:55.056
♪♪

16:55.056 --> 17:02.355
♪♪

17:02.355 --> 17:09.612
♪♪

17:13.616 --> 17:16.077
Simone: I know that look.
He's overloaded, shuttin' down.

17:16.077 --> 17:18.829
If he wasn't handcuffed to
that table, he'd be under it.

17:18.829 --> 17:21.624
Shouldn't you be on a plane
to Virginia?

17:21.624 --> 17:24.418
Oh, that's my fault.
I asked her to stay.

17:24.418 --> 17:26.712
W-Without Simone, we wouldn't
have our suspect in custody.

17:26.712 --> 17:28.172
Well, I'm glad
that she was of service.

17:28.172 --> 17:30.007
But tell me something, Trainee,
in the Bureau,

17:30.007 --> 17:31.676
what are you taught to do
when given an order?

17:31.676 --> 17:33.719
Follow it, sir,
to the letter.

17:33.719 --> 17:36.556
Matt, considering her
relationship with the suspect,

17:36.556 --> 17:38.933
we were thinking that she should
take point on the interview.

17:38.933 --> 17:40.434
Absolutely not.

17:40.434 --> 17:42.603
She's a NAT, nowhere even close
to being qualified.

17:42.603 --> 17:45.815
Garza: Agent Fox is right. We'll
conduct the interview ourselves.

17:45.815 --> 17:49.068
Get yourself back to Quantico
now, while you can.

17:50.778 --> 17:53.447
[ Door opens ]
Mr. Freemont...

17:53.447 --> 17:54.949
<i>we're with the FBI.</i>

17:54.949 --> 17:57.285
<i>You are in a lot of trouble.</i>

17:57.285 --> 17:59.912
Nolan:
I'll, um, walk you out.

17:59.912 --> 18:01.497
[ Door opens ]

18:01.497 --> 18:03.291
If you need any recommendations
on places to eat

18:03.291 --> 18:04.667
before your flight...

18:04.667 --> 18:06.752
Thanks, but I know
all the good spots.

18:06.752 --> 18:09.380
At least, I used to.
I grew up here.

18:09.380 --> 18:11.882
Really? Any family you want
to see before you leave?

18:11.882 --> 18:14.844
[ Scoffs ]
None that wants to see <i>me.</i>

18:14.844 --> 18:16.721
Fox:
Trainee, hold up!

18:16.721 --> 18:18.514
Suspect says
he'll only talk to you.

18:23.019 --> 18:24.437
Can we lose
the shackles?

18:24.437 --> 18:25.771
Yes, of course.

18:25.771 --> 18:27.398
Hey, Zeke.

18:27.398 --> 18:29.817
It's me --
Miss Clark.

18:29.817 --> 18:31.777
<i>Remember to breathe,</i>
<i>okay?</i>

18:33.988 --> 18:38.367
When I first met Zeke, he was
really struggling in school.

18:38.367 --> 18:41.704
Every day, he was either
acting out,

18:41.704 --> 18:44.498
freaking out,
or zoning out.

18:44.498 --> 18:46.751
But then we spent
some time together,

18:46.751 --> 18:49.211
and I realized he just needed
help transitioning

18:49.211 --> 18:50.838
from the chaos at home.

18:50.838 --> 18:54.467
So I told him to come
in my office every morning.

18:54.467 --> 18:56.385
And what did you say?

18:58.512 --> 18:59.889
That I didn't wanna
talk.

18:59.889 --> 19:01.140
<i>Mm-hmm, that's right.</i>

19:01.140 --> 19:02.725
And I told him
he didn't have to.

19:02.725 --> 19:04.977
He could use that time
to get quiet.

19:04.977 --> 19:07.229
And that's what we did.

19:07.229 --> 19:10.566
Every day for two years,
he would come to my office,

19:10.566 --> 19:14.779
sit for 15 minutes,
then go to class.

19:14.779 --> 19:17.907
And who became
an "A" student?

19:17.907 --> 19:20.951
Yeah, after a few weeks,
she bought me an MP3 player

19:20.951 --> 19:23.913
and some headphones so I could
listen to music in the morning.

19:23.913 --> 19:25.164
Mm-hmm.

19:27.458 --> 19:29.168
I'm in real trouble, huh?

19:29.168 --> 19:31.879
I'm afraid you are.

19:31.879 --> 19:35.383
What can you tell us about the
man with the scar on his face?

19:35.383 --> 19:38.010
I don't know who he is,
I swear.

19:38.010 --> 19:41.055
I needed money, so I've been
selling my engineering skills

19:41.055 --> 19:42.056
on the dark web.

19:42.056 --> 19:43.557
He paid you to build a bomb
for him?

19:43.557 --> 19:44.767
No,
just the detonators.

19:44.767 --> 19:47.144
Detonators?

19:47.144 --> 19:50.147
As in, more than one?

19:50.147 --> 19:54.276
I made him six,
along with a regular timer

19:54.276 --> 19:56.070
and five with GPS triggers.

19:56.070 --> 19:57.113
T-Those are special.

19:57.113 --> 19:59.573
I-I-I built them
so they'd go off

19:59.573 --> 20:01.742
when they reach a programmed set
of coordinates.

20:01.742 --> 20:03.077
And what were
the coordinates?

20:03.077 --> 20:04.453
Oh, he didn't tell me.

20:04.453 --> 20:06.706
I-I-I gave him
the instructions

20:06.706 --> 20:08.624
on how to program them in
himself.

20:08.624 --> 20:10.626
You knowingly helped
a terrorist?

20:10.626 --> 20:12.169
He said he was
a research scientist

20:12.169 --> 20:14.296
and that it was for a project
that he was working on.

20:14.296 --> 20:17.007
I-I-I knew
it didn't sound right,

20:17.007 --> 20:18.342
but I was desperate
for money.

20:18.342 --> 20:20.511
And about the time I got
to the exchange,

20:20.511 --> 20:22.388
I realized I made a mistake,
but it was too late.

20:22.388 --> 20:24.724
He grabbed the detonators
and tried to shoot me.

20:24.724 --> 20:26.142
I ran away and hid.

20:26.142 --> 20:29.019
Zeke, is there anything else you
can tell us about this man?

20:29.019 --> 20:31.188
His name,
the kind of car he drives?

20:31.188 --> 20:33.023
I told you everything I know,
man.

20:34.817 --> 20:36.444
[ <i>Crying</i> ]

20:36.444 --> 20:38.946
<i>I'm sorry I let you down,</i>
<i>Miss Clark.</i>

20:38.946 --> 20:42.032
[ Dramatic music plays ]

20:42.032 --> 20:43.200
[ <i>Sniffles</i> ]

20:43.200 --> 20:45.536
♪♪

20:45.536 --> 20:48.539
That is a very troubled
young man.

20:48.539 --> 20:50.458
You really believe he didn't
know he was making detonators

20:50.458 --> 20:52.960
for bombs?
I don't know.

20:52.960 --> 20:56.088
For such a smart kid,
he could sometimes act a fool.

20:56.088 --> 20:58.758
Now he's looking
at a lifetime of incarceration

20:58.758 --> 21:00.634
due to federal
mandatory minimums.

21:00.634 --> 21:02.470
I gotta get
this kid a lawyer.

21:02.470 --> 21:04.972
Uh, do you really think
that's a good idea?

21:04.972 --> 21:06.599
That's not gonna make you
any friends at the Bureau.

21:06.599 --> 21:09.310
I know, but Zeke's
one of my kids.

21:09.310 --> 21:11.437
I told my students
on day one,

21:11.437 --> 21:15.691
"Miss Clark will always have
your back, no matter what."

21:15.691 --> 21:18.694
That's not gonna stop
just 'cause he graduated.

21:18.694 --> 21:20.070
Is there anything
I can do to help?

21:20.070 --> 21:22.323
I appreciate that,
but I know somebody

21:22.323 --> 21:24.867
I can go to
about this.

21:24.867 --> 21:26.994
It was a pleasure
working with you, John.

21:26.994 --> 21:29.830
Wish I could stick around
to help you catch the guy.

21:29.830 --> 21:31.248
Me too.

21:31.248 --> 21:33.667
And, Simone,
don't let them get you down.

21:33.667 --> 21:35.002
You're the real thing.

21:37.963 --> 21:40.007
Lopez: Professor "Alien"
called again.

21:40.007 --> 21:43.093
He wants an update on
the Heptapod who stole his book.

21:43.093 --> 21:44.720
Well, according
to his colleagues,

21:44.720 --> 21:46.305
he was actually telling
the truth about one thing.

21:46.305 --> 21:49.350
He is the foremost expert
on urban planning.

21:49.350 --> 21:53.729
Unfortunately, he also pioneered
LSD micro-dosing.

21:53.729 --> 21:55.606
And accidentally fried
his brain?

21:55.606 --> 21:58.692
Yeah. He has been having
hallucinations ever since.

21:58.692 --> 22:01.862
[ Cellphone ringing ]

22:01.862 --> 22:04.156
Hello?

22:04.156 --> 22:07.117
Professor Meadows, we were just
discussing your case.

22:07.117 --> 22:09.954
Hold on.
Let me put you on speaker.

22:09.954 --> 22:12.206
Professor Meadows:
<i>And I just remembered something</i>
<i>about the break-in.</i>

22:12.206 --> 22:14.625
<i>When the alien fled,</i>
<i>I looked out the window</i>

22:14.625 --> 22:17.586
<i>and saw him jump</i>
<i>into a red flying saucer.</i>

22:17.586 --> 22:20.840
<i>Oh, it was more of an oval</i>
<i>now that I think about it.</i>

22:20.840 --> 22:23.759
Okay, got it. If you remember
anything else, let us know.

22:23.759 --> 22:27.513
So, should I put out a BOLO
for a red spaceship?

22:27.513 --> 22:30.224
No, but if we assume
that the attack is real,

22:30.224 --> 22:32.476
then it's possible
what he saw was a red car.

22:32.476 --> 22:34.603
So we should start pulling
traffic-cam footage.

22:34.603 --> 22:37.857
No problem. There's only about a
million red cars in Los Angeles.

22:37.857 --> 22:39.358
Hey, Grey wants
all hands on deck.

22:39.358 --> 22:41.193
Oh, thank God. [ Sighs ]

22:41.193 --> 22:44.905
Come on, people, can't rely on
the feds to solve this for us.

22:44.905 --> 22:48.117
Well, Zeke said he made
six detonators for our bomber.

22:48.117 --> 22:49.827
The first one,
a countdown timer that was used

22:49.827 --> 22:52.705
at the relay station,
and the other five GPS-enabled.

22:52.705 --> 22:54.290
If only we had an idea
what the targets are.

22:54.290 --> 22:55.958
Hey, maybe we could
extrapolate them

22:55.958 --> 22:57.710
from the first target,
the power station.

22:57.710 --> 22:59.587
There's got to be a reason
he hit that thing first.

22:59.587 --> 23:01.839
Not because he wanted
to hurt people.

23:01.839 --> 23:04.049
He only knocked out the power
to a big chunk of the Valley.

23:06.802 --> 23:08.387
What if
that was the point?

23:08.387 --> 23:11.181
What if he wanted to, uh,
get something or do something

23:11.181 --> 23:15.019
that he didn't have access to
unless the power was off?

23:15.019 --> 23:16.437
There's at least
a dozen banks.

23:16.437 --> 23:18.147
Jewelry stores,
a check-cashing place.

23:18.147 --> 23:19.607
I mean, there's no
high-value targets here.

23:19.607 --> 23:21.692
Nothing that is
a terrorist's wet dream.

23:21.692 --> 23:24.028
National Guard Armory.

23:24.028 --> 23:26.655
That --
That's gotta be it.

23:26.655 --> 23:28.824
And there are enough weapons
there for an entire platoon.

23:28.824 --> 23:32.328
And enough explosive munitions
to take out a hundred targets.

23:32.328 --> 23:34.246
[ Up-tempo music playing ]

23:34.246 --> 23:43.339
♪♪

23:43.339 --> 23:45.633
Dobbs: I'm sorry, but the
armory's in lockdown right now.

23:47.301 --> 23:50.054
I'm the one who called you
earlier...

23:50.054 --> 23:51.597
about your husband.

23:53.390 --> 23:54.850
Is Brady okay?

23:54.850 --> 23:57.019
For now.

23:57.019 --> 23:59.104
And so long as you do
as you promised,

23:59.104 --> 24:00.689
you'll see him tonight.

24:00.689 --> 24:02.149
Now, let's get to work.

24:05.986 --> 24:08.322
Tim: Control, 7-Adam-100,
be advised Adam-15,

24:08.322 --> 24:09.698
Adam-4, Adam-22, and us
are Code 3

24:09.698 --> 24:11.241
to the National Guard
Armory

24:11.241 --> 24:12.868
for a possible 459
in progress.

24:12.868 --> 24:13.911
Will advise.

24:13.911 --> 24:15.162
Bailey,
we're three minutes out.

24:15.162 --> 24:16.538
Any sign
of our terror suspect?

24:16.538 --> 24:19.708
Not yet, but the armorer chief
isn't answering his radio.

24:19.708 --> 24:21.627
[ Dramatic music playing ]

24:21.627 --> 24:26.215
♪♪

24:26.215 --> 24:27.675
We're entering the cage.

24:27.675 --> 24:32.554
♪♪

24:32.554 --> 24:34.515
Wims:
Got a man down!

24:34.515 --> 24:36.350
♪♪

24:36.350 --> 24:38.352
John, he's here.
Or he was.

24:38.352 --> 24:40.104
[ Engine revs in distance ]

24:40.104 --> 24:41.397
Stay with him.

24:41.397 --> 24:43.023
Everyone, on me.

24:43.023 --> 24:46.568
♪♪

24:46.568 --> 24:48.320
He's fleeing in one
of our Humvees.

24:48.320 --> 24:50.239
South gate.

24:50.239 --> 24:53.033
♪ It's getting hard to breathe,
take another breath ♪

24:53.033 --> 24:55.077
♪ Murder on your screen,
death is not a myth ♪

24:55.077 --> 24:57.454
[ Sirens wailing ]
There he is.

24:57.454 --> 25:00.290
7-Adam-100, suspect vehicle
heading west on Vernon.

25:00.290 --> 25:01.583
Show us in pursuit.

25:01.583 --> 25:04.003
♪ It'll have you pumping
like Reeboks ♪

25:04.003 --> 25:05.796
[ Tires screech ]
Whoa, whoa.

25:05.796 --> 25:07.047
[ Horn honking ]

25:07.047 --> 25:08.340
♪ You looking at a savage,
run for cover ♪

25:08.340 --> 25:09.341
Geez.

25:09.341 --> 25:11.051
♪♪

25:11.051 --> 25:12.553
♪ Run for cover ♪

25:12.553 --> 25:13.887
We need to stop
this guy.

25:13.887 --> 25:15.556
That's not a minivan,
it's a mini-tank.

25:15.556 --> 25:16.849
Bulletproof, bombproof.

25:16.849 --> 25:17.975
Our shops
can't pit-maneuver it.

25:17.975 --> 25:19.393
We have to wait
for the BearCat.

25:19.393 --> 25:21.478
Maybe we can box the Humvee in,
force him off the road.

25:21.478 --> 25:22.730
There's one way
we can find out.

25:22.730 --> 25:25.399
♪ Chills around your body,
it's a cold war ♪

25:25.399 --> 25:27.443
Okay, Nolan, get on his left.
We'll take the right.

25:27.443 --> 25:28.777
[ Sirens wailing ]

25:28.777 --> 25:31.196
You have to ram him in unison,
alright?

25:31.196 --> 25:32.448
Aim for the doors.

25:32.448 --> 25:33.907
Whatever you do,
don't hit the wheels.

25:33.907 --> 25:35.409
What? Why? What happens
if I hit his wheels?

25:35.409 --> 25:37.036
We'll die,
and you'll forever be known

25:37.036 --> 25:38.620
as an LAPD cautionary tale.

25:38.620 --> 25:40.289
Oh, great, proving my mother
right once and for all.

25:40.289 --> 25:41.957
Wait. <i>I'll</i> be
the cautionary tale?

25:41.957 --> 25:43.542
No way.
If this goes bad,

25:43.542 --> 25:45.252
we will both be disgraced
together.

25:45.252 --> 25:47.755
In position.
Alright, on three.

25:47.755 --> 25:49.423
One, two, three!

25:49.423 --> 25:50.758
[ Tires screech ]

25:50.758 --> 25:53.260
[ Metal crunching ]

25:53.260 --> 25:55.888
[ Tires screeching ]

25:55.888 --> 25:58.932
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

25:58.932 --> 26:01.643
♪♪

26:01.643 --> 26:03.604
Show me your hands!
Now!

26:03.604 --> 26:05.481
♪ Run for cover ♪

26:05.481 --> 26:07.316
♪♪

26:07.316 --> 26:08.859
♪ Run for cover ♪

26:08.859 --> 26:11.653
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

26:11.653 --> 26:14.448
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

26:14.448 --> 26:23.290
♪♪

26:25.793 --> 26:27.836
[ Knock on door ]

26:27.836 --> 26:29.463
Hey, Daddy.

26:29.463 --> 26:31.548
What are you doing
in L. A.?

26:31.548 --> 26:35.302
Uh, you'd know if you answered
my calls or my texts or my --

26:35.302 --> 26:38.347
Are you still
in the FBI?

26:38.347 --> 26:41.600
Technically, I'm just a trainee,
but...

26:42.309 --> 26:44.645
He did not just close this door
in my face.

26:44.645 --> 26:46.814
Daddy!

26:46.814 --> 26:48.982
Open the door.
We need to talk.

26:50.317 --> 26:51.944
Are my grandkids okay?

26:51.944 --> 26:53.403
The twins are fine.

26:53.403 --> 26:55.239
Then there's nothing for us
to talk about.

26:55.239 --> 26:56.824
Uh...

26:56.824 --> 26:58.158
Open this damn door!

26:58.158 --> 27:00.619
[ Dog barking ]
Da--

27:00.619 --> 27:03.956
Your neighbors are out here
looking at me like I'm crazy.

27:03.956 --> 27:05.958
Hey, Mr. Jenkins.

27:05.958 --> 27:09.128
Your dog is so cute.
[ Chuckles ]

27:09.128 --> 27:10.921
This is embarrassing!

27:10.921 --> 27:13.006
Not as embarrassing
as being a leader

27:13.006 --> 27:15.551
in the "Defund The Police"
movement

27:15.551 --> 27:18.887
with a daughter
in the FBI.

27:18.887 --> 27:22.474
Do not close this door,
you stubborn old man.

27:22.474 --> 27:25.018
If you don't want to talk to
your only daughter, fine.

27:25.018 --> 27:26.895
But I'm not here
as your daughter.

27:26.895 --> 27:28.897
I'm here as an advocate.

27:30.023 --> 27:32.526
For who?
Zeke Freemont.

27:32.526 --> 27:34.361
He's one
of my former students.

27:34.361 --> 27:36.738
Now he's being charged
as an accessory

27:36.738 --> 27:38.574
in a domestic terror
plot.

27:38.574 --> 27:41.368
And you're the only person
I trust to get him a lawyer

27:41.368 --> 27:43.412
that'll actually
give a damn.

27:43.412 --> 27:44.746
[ Sighs ]
So, see?

27:44.746 --> 27:46.623
This is not about
you and me.

27:46.623 --> 27:49.960
This is about a kid
who deserves a second chance.

27:51.253 --> 27:54.089
So, will you help me?

27:54.089 --> 27:56.049
♪ And that's cool, my man,
it's all a part of the plan ♪

27:56.049 --> 27:58.886
♪ Found the source of
inspiration so united we stand ♪
[ Sighs ]

27:58.886 --> 28:01.013
♪ Back to back, side to side,
soon all will see ♪

28:01.013 --> 28:04.391
[ Police radio chatter ]

28:05.559 --> 28:07.561
My husband was abducted
by this man.

28:07.561 --> 28:09.897
He threatened to kill Brady if I
didn't do exactly what he said.

28:09.897 --> 28:11.440
Okay.
Can you describe him?

28:11.440 --> 28:14.109
Russian -- at least, his accent.
Scar on his face.

28:14.109 --> 28:16.153
What did he steal
from my armory?

28:16.153 --> 28:19.114
200 kilos
of C-4 explosives.

28:19.114 --> 28:21.783
[ Dramatic music plays ]

28:25.287 --> 28:27.623
Now, nobody asked you
to cook.

28:27.623 --> 28:29.833
Okay, you want me
to throw it out?

28:29.833 --> 28:31.919
♪♪

28:31.919 --> 28:34.087
Mmm!
Okay?

28:34.087 --> 28:37.132
Mm-hmm. It tastes just like
your mother's.

28:37.132 --> 28:38.425
[ Dizzy Gillespie's "Sumphin'"
plays ]

28:38.425 --> 28:40.427
Miles Davis.
I love this song.

28:40.427 --> 28:43.764
Yeah, me too,
but it's Dizzy Gillespie.

28:43.764 --> 28:45.933
Bup-bup-bup-bup.
Back up.

28:45.933 --> 28:48.435
Don't even come over here
reaching in these pots.

28:48.435 --> 28:50.520
Mama's recipe,
Mama's rules.

28:50.520 --> 28:52.564
We eat at the table.

28:52.564 --> 28:56.318
Oh, I miss everything
about your mother...

28:56.318 --> 28:58.862
except her damn rules.

28:58.862 --> 29:00.530
[ Laughs ]

29:00.530 --> 29:03.659
You would always rope me in
as your accomplice

29:03.659 --> 29:06.495
to break every single
last one of them.

29:06.495 --> 29:09.164
We drove Mama crazy
with our foolishness.

29:09.164 --> 29:11.083
[ Chuckling ] Yeah.

29:11.083 --> 29:13.794
♪♪

29:13.794 --> 29:17.297
We used to be
so close, Daddy.

29:17.297 --> 29:19.716
Well, that's on you.

29:19.716 --> 29:22.636
Joining the feds,
after everything I went through

29:22.636 --> 29:24.304
at the hands
of law enforcement --

29:24.304 --> 29:26.723
Everything
<i>we</i> went through.

29:26.723 --> 29:30.519
Really? Because I was
the one incarcerated

29:30.519 --> 29:32.854
for a crime
I didn't commit,

29:32.854 --> 29:35.565
away from you,
your mother.

29:35.565 --> 29:38.360
Which is why I'll find
a lawyer

29:38.360 --> 29:39.945
for your student
who is in trouble.

29:39.945 --> 29:44.157
But, Simone, you are on
the wrong side of this trouble.

29:44.157 --> 29:47.661
It was an FBI investigation
that got you exonerated.

29:47.661 --> 29:52.207
And it was FBI investigations
that tried to compromise Martin,

29:52.207 --> 29:55.585
Malcolm, Angela,
Black Lives Matter.

29:55.585 --> 29:59.214
Daddy, a good agent can make
more positive change

29:59.214 --> 30:02.050
with one case than most people
do in a lifetime.

30:02.050 --> 30:05.387
Oh, what's that?
Quote for the yearbook?

30:05.387 --> 30:08.890
Come on, give me a real reason
why you are doing this.

30:08.890 --> 30:12.060
Because we make up
less than 1%.

30:12.060 --> 30:15.981
Black women make up
less than 1% of the FBI.

30:15.981 --> 30:18.900
Speeches at rallies
only do so much.

30:18.900 --> 30:23.697
If we want real justice,
we need a voice on the inside.

30:23.697 --> 30:25.282
You just don't get it.

30:25.282 --> 30:29.244
Once you're in the FBI,
they'll change you.

30:29.244 --> 30:32.205
♪♪

30:32.205 --> 30:34.458
Well,
we will never know.

30:34.458 --> 30:38.336
'Cause I am about that close
to being kicked out.

30:38.336 --> 30:41.173
♪♪

30:41.173 --> 30:42.716
For what?

30:42.716 --> 30:45.802
Well, apparently, there two ways
of doing things --

30:45.802 --> 30:48.263
the FBI way
and the wrong way.

30:48.263 --> 30:51.224
And guess which one
I'm excelling in.

30:51.224 --> 30:52.559
So I'm screwed.

30:52.559 --> 30:54.895
Not according to
Miles Davis.

30:54.895 --> 30:58.231
He said, "When you hit
a wrong note,

30:58.231 --> 31:01.777
it's the next note
that makes it good or bad."

31:01.777 --> 31:03.737
They haven't
kicked you out yet.

31:03.737 --> 31:06.114
So what happens next
is on you.

31:06.114 --> 31:07.949
It's great advice,
Daddy,

31:07.949 --> 31:10.952
but I thought you said you
didn't want me to be in the FBI.

31:10.952 --> 31:12.996
No, I don't.

31:12.996 --> 31:18.335
But nobody tells my baby girl
that she doesn't belong.

31:18.335 --> 31:23.381
♪♪

31:23.381 --> 31:26.343
Wow. The FBI doesn't really do
moderation, do they?

31:26.343 --> 31:28.386
Seriously, it's like
a spaceship.

31:28.386 --> 31:31.598
Get any sleep?
No, but, uh,
Sleeping Beauty here

31:31.598 --> 31:32.974
got an hour
in the back of the shop.

31:32.974 --> 31:34.559
Sergeant's stripes
come with privileges.

31:34.559 --> 31:35.811
[ Door opens ]
Don't be jealous.

31:35.811 --> 31:38.730
Okay, people, listen up.
Garza has an update.

31:38.730 --> 31:40.232
Garza:
It's a whole new ballgame.

31:40.232 --> 31:42.192
The amount of explosives stolen
sent shock waves

31:42.192 --> 31:43.777
through D. C. overnight.

31:43.777 --> 31:46.238
Homeland Security is now getting
involved, as is ATF,

31:46.238 --> 31:49.032
which means this is no longer
a joint task force.

31:49.032 --> 31:50.617
It's wholly federal now.

31:50.617 --> 31:53.161
All due respect, LAPD has busted
their ass in this case.

31:53.161 --> 31:54.621
Hey, I get it.

31:54.621 --> 31:56.665
I do,
but my hands are tied.

31:56.665 --> 31:59.167
A terrorist got away with
over 200 kilos of C-4,

31:59.167 --> 32:01.169
so that kind of changes
the complexion of things.

32:01.169 --> 32:03.797
Are you blaming my guys
for that?
Did I say that, Wade?

32:03.797 --> 32:06.049
Oh, no, uh,
we're all a little tired,

32:06.049 --> 32:08.927
but I think we can remember
we're all on the same team here.

32:08.927 --> 32:11.179
You're not talking
to security guards, Matt.

32:11.179 --> 32:14.015
We've investigators, and we're
not gonna stop hunting this guy

32:14.015 --> 32:15.475
because you tell us to.

32:15.475 --> 32:17.894
Can we talk about this
in private, please?

32:17.894 --> 32:20.313
You're damn straight.

32:20.313 --> 32:22.566
My office.
[ Sighs ]

32:22.566 --> 32:23.650
[ Door opens ]

32:25.819 --> 32:27.362
I got a problem.
Me too.

32:27.362 --> 32:29.281
I've been scrubbing traffic-cam
footage for hours,

32:29.281 --> 32:31.158
hunting for
an extraterrestrial.

32:31.158 --> 32:33.368
No, no, I'm serious.

32:33.368 --> 32:35.162
What is it?
The baby?

32:35.162 --> 32:36.913
No. [ Sighs ]

32:36.913 --> 32:39.833
TID pulled partial prints
from the professor's rear door.

32:39.833 --> 32:42.252
You know, the one that
the aliens jimmied open?

32:42.252 --> 32:43.628
That's not a problem.
That's great.

32:43.628 --> 32:44.963
It has to belong
to the attacker.

32:44.963 --> 32:47.048
Exactly.
So I ran the prints,

32:47.048 --> 32:49.009
and they came back
as classified.

32:49.009 --> 32:51.386
What?
Yeah, so,
I called my friend

32:51.386 --> 32:54.431
over at the DEA
who has top-secret clearance,

32:54.431 --> 32:56.057
and I asked her to run
the prints,

32:56.057 --> 32:58.560
and she was denied
access, too.

32:58.560 --> 33:00.478
Who the hell
is our suspect?

33:00.478 --> 33:03.023
I don't know,
but the classified designation

33:03.023 --> 33:06.651
for our suspect
originated from...

33:06.651 --> 33:11.323
the Air Force base
at Groom Lake.

33:11.323 --> 33:12.908
Okay,
your vocal inflection

33:12.908 --> 33:14.117
leads me to believe
that's a big deal,

33:14.117 --> 33:15.952
but for the life of me,
I don't know why.

33:15.952 --> 33:18.079
How do you not know
about Groom Lake?

33:18.079 --> 33:20.540
Paradise Ranch?
Dreamland?

33:20.540 --> 33:23.126
Also known as Area 51.

33:23.126 --> 33:25.629
Isn't that where the government
supposedly keeps the --

33:25.629 --> 33:28.798
Aliens? Yeah.

33:35.055 --> 33:37.933
Sgt. Grey:
You think I'm pissed off because
you hurt our feelings?

33:37.933 --> 33:40.060
We don't care...
What the hell
are you still doing here?

33:40.060 --> 33:42.562
Oh, I just need five minutes
with Agent Garza.

33:42.562 --> 33:44.356
You're supposed to be back
at Quantico.

33:44.356 --> 33:46.816
You and I both know that as soon
as I get back to the Academy,

33:46.816 --> 33:48.652
they gonna find
a reason to fire me.

33:48.652 --> 33:50.987
Here is the only place
I can prove I belong.

33:50.987 --> 33:53.823
You're still a trainee.
It's not gonna happen.

33:53.823 --> 33:56.451
Can you honestly say that
all my contributions

33:56.451 --> 33:58.286
haven't earned me a place
on this task force?

33:58.286 --> 33:59.788
Absolutely.

33:59.788 --> 34:02.666
A NAT who can't follow orders
has no place in the FBI.

34:02.666 --> 34:06.253
Okay. Look...my father
was incarcerated

34:06.253 --> 34:07.754
for a crime
he didn't commit.

34:07.754 --> 34:09.965
I know.
I read your file.

34:09.965 --> 34:12.425
Okay, w-well,
here's what's not in it.

34:12.425 --> 34:15.345
My father was
an amazing trumpet player.

34:15.345 --> 34:17.138
He was a jazz prodigy.

34:17.138 --> 34:19.099
After eight years
in prison,

34:19.099 --> 34:21.142
never picked up
his horn again.

34:21.142 --> 34:22.936
He let the system steal
that from him.

34:22.936 --> 34:24.437
He didn't even put up
a fight.

34:24.437 --> 34:27.315
He gave up on his music,
his dreams, all of it.

34:27.315 --> 34:29.859
But let me guess.
It's not gonna be you.

34:29.859 --> 34:34.155
Look at you,
finally starting to get me.

34:34.155 --> 34:35.824
Let me tell you
what I wish someone told me

34:35.824 --> 34:39.160
when I was a blue flamer,
trying to prove myself.

34:39.160 --> 34:42.330
The FBI isn't a safe space
for women's empowerment.

34:42.330 --> 34:44.040
It's a boys' club.

34:44.040 --> 34:46.501
Now, you still have
a chance to make it.
[ Sighs ]

34:46.501 --> 34:49.004
All you have to do is fit in
by hiding who you really are.

34:49.004 --> 34:51.339
Honey, there's
no hiding this.

34:51.339 --> 34:54.009
Simone, I'm trying
to help you.

34:54.009 --> 34:57.637
I know, Casey --
Agent Fox.

34:57.637 --> 35:00.223
A-And I'm sorry for whatever
you had to put up with

35:00.223 --> 35:01.725
to do this job.

35:01.725 --> 35:03.893
But the one thing I learned
in this life

35:03.893 --> 35:05.687
is to be true
to who I am.

35:05.687 --> 35:09.524
So I'm waiting right here
for Agent Garza.

35:09.524 --> 35:11.359
Okay.

35:11.359 --> 35:12.736
Lopez:
Here's what we're gonna do.

35:12.736 --> 35:14.279
I'm gonna call a professional...
[ Sighs ]

35:14.279 --> 35:15.530
...someone you could talk to
about all of this.

35:15.530 --> 35:17.365
But you're working
with the aliens.

35:17.365 --> 35:20.535
No, Professor, we are the ones
who are trying to help you.

35:20.535 --> 35:23.705
We believe that your attacker
is or was in the military.

35:23.705 --> 35:26.207
Yes,
the galactic alien army.

35:26.207 --> 35:29.502
Okay, okay, maybe your attacker
was an alien.

35:29.502 --> 35:33.590
The truth finally prevails
with you conniving WIBs.

35:33.590 --> 35:35.091
WIBs?

35:35.091 --> 35:36.509
Simone: Women in Black.

35:36.509 --> 35:38.428
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

35:38.428 --> 35:42.015
Hi, y'all.
I'm Simone with the FBI.

35:42.015 --> 35:44.267
Can I speak to you two
for a hot sec?

35:44.267 --> 35:48.605
♪♪

35:48.605 --> 35:52.108
Hey, I'm not trying to tell you
how to do your job,

35:52.108 --> 35:54.778
but that man is having
a clinical delusion.

35:54.778 --> 35:58.615
He's unable to process logic,
so you challenging him

35:58.615 --> 36:01.326
is only pushing him further
towards his beliefs.

36:01.326 --> 36:04.329
And you playing along
is just making him think

36:04.329 --> 36:06.331
his delusions are real.

36:06.331 --> 36:09.084
Are you a psychiatrist
or...

36:09.084 --> 36:10.585
I was
a guidance counselor.

36:10.585 --> 36:13.296
I worked with kids
experiencing everything

36:13.296 --> 36:16.633
from schizoaffective disorder
to severe horniness.

36:16.633 --> 36:18.551
So, you think you can
get through to him

36:18.551 --> 36:19.886
in a way that we can't?

36:19.886 --> 36:22.389
I think I can charm
and disarm him,

36:22.389 --> 36:24.224
and it might bring him back
to reality.

36:24.224 --> 36:26.643
We could definitely use
some more reality.

36:26.643 --> 36:28.103
Give it a try.

36:28.103 --> 36:32.774
Simone: Hello, sir.
I am not a Woman in Black.

36:32.774 --> 36:35.110
See?
I'm wearing brown and tan.

36:35.110 --> 36:37.445
It's cute, right?

36:37.445 --> 36:40.782
Mind if we go somewhere
where we could talk?

36:40.782 --> 36:43.993
When I was a little girl,
I used to go out in the yard

36:43.993 --> 36:45.787
and look for UFOs.

36:45.787 --> 36:48.540
And then, one night,
they found me.

36:48.540 --> 36:49.791
Extraterrestrials?

36:49.791 --> 36:52.419
Well, no,
a family of possums

36:52.419 --> 36:55.004
rooting around
in our trash cans.

36:55.004 --> 36:56.631
I thought
they were ETs.

36:56.631 --> 36:59.259
Have you ever seen
one of those things up close?

36:59.259 --> 37:01.261
It's otherworldly.

37:01.261 --> 37:04.931
But I never stopped believing
that it was possible

37:04.931 --> 37:06.850
we're not alone
in the universe.

37:06.850 --> 37:08.601
We're not.

37:08.601 --> 37:12.981
I was attacked by a Heptapod who
smelled of chocolate and blood.

37:12.981 --> 37:17.527
Okay, see, now, Professor,
that makes me wonder

37:17.527 --> 37:23.366
why you're the only person
who saw this bizarre creature.

37:23.366 --> 37:26.494
Because he's a shape-shifter
who can take on many forms.

37:26.494 --> 37:28.830
Okay. Like what?

37:28.830 --> 37:32.000
A white man in his 30s.

37:32.000 --> 37:34.461
Okay, what else can you tell me
about him,

37:34.461 --> 37:36.963
when he was a white man
in his 30s?

37:36.963 --> 37:39.174
He spoke Russian.

37:39.174 --> 37:40.467
Well, at least,
he had an accent.

37:40.467 --> 37:41.718
It's hard to remember.

37:41.718 --> 37:43.470
W-Well, Professor,

37:43.470 --> 37:47.724
did the man have a scar
on the left side of his face?

37:47.724 --> 37:49.142
You've seen him, too.

37:49.142 --> 37:50.477
I'll be right back.

37:50.477 --> 37:52.103
[ Dramatic music plays ]

37:52.103 --> 37:53.813
Do you have
a task force BOLO?

37:53.813 --> 37:55.482
I can pull it up
on my phone.

37:57.358 --> 37:59.861
Professor...
is this the man

37:59.861 --> 38:02.655
that attacked you
inside your home?

38:02.655 --> 38:04.699
Yes! That's him.

38:09.871 --> 38:11.873
Okay, everybody, our suspect
is renting a house

38:11.873 --> 38:13.166
in Lincoln Heights under
the name Trevor Gurin.

38:13.166 --> 38:14.667
We tracked him there through
traffic-cam footage

38:14.667 --> 38:16.127
from his origin point
at the professor's house.

38:16.127 --> 38:17.545
That's great work,
detectives.

38:17.545 --> 38:18.838
Actually, Simone deserves
the credit.

38:18.838 --> 38:20.673
She's the one who put it
all together.

38:20.673 --> 38:23.968
♪♪

38:23.968 --> 38:25.261
Good work.

38:25.261 --> 38:26.513
Thank you, sir.
I just --

38:26.513 --> 38:28.431
Mobilize additional agents
and HRT.

38:28.431 --> 38:30.016
And notify Homeland
and ATF.

38:30.016 --> 38:31.309
So, you two on me.

38:31.309 --> 38:33.061
Get schematics for the house,
send them to my box.

38:33.061 --> 38:34.896
I'll put in
for a telephonic warrant.
Alright.

38:34.896 --> 38:36.940
[ Indistinct conversations ]

38:36.940 --> 38:45.740
♪♪

38:45.740 --> 38:48.409
Garza: So, you think I should
put you on the task force?

38:51.037 --> 38:54.332
Honestly, only a fool
would keep me off it.

38:54.332 --> 38:56.376
Are you calling me
a fool?

38:56.376 --> 38:58.920
Are you putting me
on the task force?

39:01.297 --> 39:04.175
Yeah.
[ Chuckles ]

39:04.175 --> 39:05.802
You're riding with me.
Let's go.

39:05.802 --> 39:07.512
[ Up-tempo music plays ]

39:07.512 --> 39:08.847
Yes!

39:11.140 --> 39:12.767
Officer #1: Go, go, go!

39:12.767 --> 39:15.186
Officer #2:
Secure the perimeter.

39:15.186 --> 39:16.437
Nolan:
We got a body!

39:16.437 --> 39:17.856
Is it our suspect?

39:17.856 --> 39:20.441
No, the abducted husband.

39:20.441 --> 39:22.694
Given how cold he is, I'd say
Gurin killed him last night

39:22.694 --> 39:24.904
when he got back
from stealing the explosives.

39:24.904 --> 39:26.573
House is clear.
For all we know,

39:26.573 --> 39:28.366
this guy's pulling off
his next attacks as we speak.

39:28.366 --> 39:30.201
So let's tear this place apart.
We're looking for anything

39:30.201 --> 39:32.245
that might indicate
our unsub's targets.

39:32.245 --> 39:35.456
Man: <i>All units, be advised</i>
<i>suspect still at large.</i>

39:35.456 --> 39:38.251
<i>Male Caucasian,</i>
<i>armed and dangerous.</i>

39:38.251 --> 39:40.253
Hey,
I-I think this is a map.

39:40.253 --> 39:41.838
It has to have been
of L. A.,

39:41.838 --> 39:43.548
and there were
other pins in it.

39:43.548 --> 39:45.049
If we could
find the publisher,

39:45.049 --> 39:47.677
maybe we could match
the pinholes with locations?

39:47.677 --> 39:49.512
Yeah. On it.
We got a whole department

39:49.512 --> 39:51.681
of eggheads who love solving
these kinds of puzzles.

39:51.681 --> 39:52.932
You got something?

39:52.932 --> 39:54.267
There's no mattress
in there.

39:54.267 --> 39:56.561
This guy was just sleeping
on a hard-ass floor.

39:56.561 --> 39:57.770
Alright, so, what do you think
it means?

39:57.770 --> 39:59.480
He's punishing himself.

39:59.480 --> 40:02.066
Nothing soft, nothing warm,
no creature comforts.

40:02.066 --> 40:03.776
Military man, maybe?

40:03.776 --> 40:05.486
Used to sleeping on the ground?
Finds a bed too soft?

40:05.486 --> 40:07.238
Or maybe too indulgent.

40:07.238 --> 40:09.240
So, what's a better way
to stay focused on the mission

40:09.240 --> 40:10.992
than to take away
every small pleasure?

40:10.992 --> 40:11.993
Sure, that tracks.

40:11.993 --> 40:13.286
What I can't
wrap my mind around

40:13.286 --> 40:15.163
is the connection
to Area 51.

40:15.163 --> 40:16.748
Why would they classify
his fingerprints?

40:16.748 --> 40:20.627
You know, stories about aliens
at Area 51 were only a cover

40:20.627 --> 40:22.545
that they were doing
covert operations there.

40:22.545 --> 40:23.838
So, what are we saying?

40:23.838 --> 40:27.091
Our suspect had ties
to classified U. S. operations?

40:27.091 --> 40:28.468
Geez, what a nightmare
that would be.

40:28.468 --> 40:30.094
Chen found something.

40:30.094 --> 40:32.472
Uh, I figured he would write
on the map,

40:32.472 --> 40:33.640
so I did a wall rubbing.

40:33.640 --> 40:34.807
Uh, I found a word.

40:34.807 --> 40:37.644
It's faint,
but I think it says "Enervo."

40:37.644 --> 40:40.855
What does that mean?
It's Latin.
It means "to deprive of power."

40:40.855 --> 40:43.107
Yeah, I worked with a lot of CIA
guys in Afghanistan,

40:43.107 --> 40:44.442
and Enervo is just the type

40:44.442 --> 40:46.235
of pretentious code name
they'd give an op.

40:46.235 --> 40:47.820
"Deprive of power"
is exactly

40:47.820 --> 40:49.155
what he was doing
with the first bombing.

40:49.155 --> 40:51.074
You think he'd go after
more relay stations?

40:51.074 --> 40:54.285
No. In a ground war, what's
the military's first target?

40:54.285 --> 40:55.870
Take out the enemy's
infrastructure.

40:55.870 --> 40:57.413
Power, water --
Roads.

40:58.164 --> 41:01.167
That's why he stole the
professor's book on traffic.

41:01.167 --> 41:03.878
Quickest way to cripple this
city -- take out the freeways.

41:03.878 --> 41:06.923
[ Beeping ]

41:06.923 --> 41:10.009
[ Dramatic music plays ]

41:10.009 --> 41:19.018
♪♪

41:19.018 --> 41:22.438
Hello.
I'm Professor Meadows.

41:22.438 --> 41:24.482
I'm so pleased you all agreed
to help me

41:24.482 --> 41:25.942
with my little
research project

41:25.942 --> 41:28.403
on traffic patterns
in Los Angeles.

41:28.403 --> 41:30.571
Inside the envelope,
you'll find your first payment

41:30.571 --> 41:33.908
and your precise driving route
for the day.

41:33.908 --> 41:35.368
It's vital

41:35.368 --> 41:37.912
that you follow the exact
directions in your envelope.

41:37.912 --> 41:41.124
Otherwise, you won't get
your delivery payment.

41:42.709 --> 41:45.461
Excellent.
Then get going.

41:45.461 --> 41:47.672
And remember -- drive safe.

41:47.672 --> 41:49.549
♪♪

41:49.549 --> 41:51.509
Alright,
let's get going.

